Portfolio 6

Cynthia Jiao

4/3/2025

I will be doing the last exploratory analyses of my thesis data for this portfolio. This is a zip code analysis of the effect of neighborhood diversity (proportion of minority population) on children’s stereotyping choices (spolier alert it’s not significant), plus a map showing the participants’ zip code distribution.

Do exposure to neighborhood diversity affect children’s choice? (zip code analysis)

Exposure to neighborhood diversity does not influence children’s choice ( B = -0.49, F(1. 1434) = 2.25, p = 0.13). Also no significant interaction effect involving neighborhood diversity was found (all ps > 0.1).
